</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D1B6652E4D20483AFF03FC584A2E304D" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="991336A54D20483AFF03FC584A2E304D" blockId="43.[151,1437,331,1365]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="ABD8EAB74D20483AFF03FC584A4A36D1" bold="true" box="[199,315,943,969]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Remarks.</emphasis>
Our material of 
<taxonomicName id="5EAC4D264D20483AFE38FC47498436D1" authorityName="van Soest &amp; de Weerdt" authorityYear="2001" box="[508,757,944,969]" class="Demospongiae" family="Petrosiidae" genus="Xestospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="arenosa">
<emphasis id="ABD8EAB74D20483AFE38FC47498436D1" box="[508,757,944,969]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Xestospongia arenosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
constitutes the first record of the species for the GoM. The present material’s overall features are similar to those from the original description, distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName id="5EAC4D264D20483AFAAEFC234A2E3109" class="Demospongiae" family="Petrosiidae" genus="Xestospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="ABD8EAB74D20483AFAAEFC234A743109" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Xestospongia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by its loose reticulation, mainly of single spicules. Our specimens were inside the coral rubble with only a portion of their body exposed on the surface, contrasting to the massive morphology of specimens from 
<bibRefCitation id="FD3D4B544D20483AFF53FBB74A973141" author="van Soest, R. W. M. &amp; Weerdt de, W. H." box="[151,486,1087,1114]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="109 - 118" refId="ref81974" refString="van Soest, R. W. M. &amp; Weerdt de, W. H. (2001) New records of Xestospongia species (Haplosclerida: Petrosidae) from the Curacao reefs, with a description of a new species. Beaufortia, 51, 109 - 118." type="journal article" year="2001">van Soest &amp; de Weerdt (2001)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="FD3D4B544D20483AFDDFFBC849843141" author="Silva, J. A. &amp; Zea, S." box="[539,757,1087,1114]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="113 - 136" refId="ref81331" refString="Silva, J. A. &amp; Zea, S. (2017) New records of sponges of the genera Petrosia and Xestospongia (Demospongiae: Haplosclerida: Petrosiidae) from the Colombian Caribbean. Boletin de Investigaciones Marinas y Costeras, 46, 113 - 136. https: // doi. org / 10.25268 / bimc. invemar. 2017.46.1.718" type="journal article" year="2017">Silva &amp; Zea (2017)</bibRefCitation>
. Characteristics matching our specimens and those described in 
<bibRefCitation id="FD3D4B544D20483AFF72FB9349613165" author="van Soest, R. W. M. &amp; Weerdt de, W. H." box="[182,528,1123,1150]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="109 - 118" refId="ref81974" refString="van Soest, R. W. M. &amp; Weerdt de, W. H. (2001) New records of Xestospongia species (Haplosclerida: Petrosidae) from the Curacao reefs, with a description of a new species. Beaufortia, 51, 109 - 118." type="journal article" year="2001">van Soest &amp; de Weerdt (2001)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="FD3D4B544D20483AFD8EFB9448593165" author="Silva, J. A. &amp; Zea, S." box="[586,808,1123,1150]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="113 - 136" refId="ref81331" refString="Silva, J. A. &amp; Zea, S. (2017) New records of sponges of the genera Petrosia and Xestospongia (Demospongiae: Haplosclerida: Petrosiidae) from the Colombian Caribbean. Boletin de Investigaciones Marinas y Costeras, 46, 113 - 136. https: // doi. org / 10.25268 / bimc. invemar. 2017.46.1.718" type="journal article" year="2017">Silva &amp; Zea (2017)</bibRefCitation>
are the ectosomal skeleton with a unispicular isotropic reticulation, the triangular meshes, and the loose choanosomal skeleton with a reticulation of ascending primary spicule tracts. The length of spicules in our specimens were slightly smaller (250– 
<emphasis id="ABD8EAB74D20483AFBE5FB5C4F3A31DD" box="[1057,1099,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">375</emphasis>
(50.1)–420/8.5– 
<emphasis id="ABD8EAB74D20483AFAC2FB5C4E4631DD" box="[1286,1335,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">14.3</emphasis>
(3.3)–19 µm) than in specimens recorded by 
<bibRefCitation id="FD3D4B544D20483AFDE9FB2748F631F1" author="van Soest, R. W. M. &amp; Weerdt de, W. H." box="[557,903,1231,1258]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="109 - 118" refId="ref81974" refString="van Soest, R. W. M. &amp; Weerdt de, W. H. (2001) New records of Xestospongia species (Haplosclerida: Petrosidae) from the Curacao reefs, with a description of a new species. Beaufortia, 51, 109 - 118." type="journal article" year="2001">van Soest &amp; de Weerdt (2001)</bibRefCitation>
: 342–431.2–508 × 7–10.1–14 µm, and 
<bibRefCitation id="FD3D4B544D20483AFA81FB384A663015" author="Silva, J. A. &amp; Zea, S." pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="113 - 136" refId="ref81331" refString="Silva, J. A. &amp; Zea, S. (2017) New records of sponges of the genera Petrosia and Xestospongia (Demospongiae: Haplosclerida: Petrosiidae) from the Colombian Caribbean. Boletin de Investigaciones Marinas y Costeras, 46, 113 - 136. https: // doi. org / 10.25268 / bimc. invemar. 2017.46.1.718" type="journal article" year="2017">Silva &amp; Zea (2017)</bibRefCitation>
: 300–436–508 × 16–19–29.2 µm. This difference in the spicules proportions could be due to the lower amounts of silica available in the GoM compared to other regions in the Atlantic ocean (
<bibRefCitation id="FD3D4B544D20483AFBB7FAE04A22304D" author="Lanza-Espino de la, G. &amp; Gomez-Rojas, J." pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="41 - 61" refId="ref77778" refString="Lanza-Espino de la, G. &amp; Gomez-Rojas, J. (2004) Physical and chemical characteristics of the stratigraphy. In: Withers, K. &amp; Nipper, M. (Eds.), Environmental Analysis of the Gulf of Mexico. Harte Research Institute for Gulf of Mexico Studies Special Publication Series No. 1. Harte Research Institute for Gulf of Mexico Studies, Mexico city, pp. 41 - 61." type="book chapter" year="2004">Lanza-Espino de la &amp; Gómez-Rojas 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
